reviews.title: Delicious food in an atmospheric location
reviews.text: With 19 guests we held our wedding dinner here. Perfectly cared for. A delicious dinner with good meat, delicious fish and also options for our vegan guests. The atmosphere is perfect, welcoming reception and beautiful location. Highly recommended!

reviews.title: It was the whole experience worth 5 stars 🌟.
reviews.text: Very warmly received by the hostess Anita. The food was delicious. A beautiful restaurant and very attentively served. The hostess was interested thought along. Highly recommended!

reviews.title: Not five stars but six stars ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
reviews.text: When we are in Epe again, we will treat ourselves to dinner or lunch at the Veldhoeve at least once. Anita, the exceptionally hospitable hostess, always makes us feel very welcome. And André, her husband, cooks the stars from heaven. And when the weather is nice, the Veldhoeve terrace is the most beautiful terrace in the Netherlands!

reviews.title: A wonderful evening out in a nice environment.
reviews.text:
A perfect place in a separate room for 8 people.
Great service and they think along about what to eat and drink. You feel at home and you are well taken care of!

reviews.title: Everything you want from a wonderful (and delicious) night out
reviews.text:
While cycling in Epe we passed by Restaurant De Veldhoeve and we decided to make a reservation for diner that evening. They gave us the opportunity to choose a specific table (if we wanted) inside with the alternative of dining outside if the weather would permit so. 
That evening we were greeted very friendly and helpful. And after checking the menu plus winelist we we were offered a delightful appetizer. As main courses we chose the salmon and fillet of sirloin. Which proved to be a very good choice: both beautiful prepared and served and of great taste.  Chef cook mr. Licht did a wonderful job, and so did our host mrs. Bakker: friendly, helpful and constantly around for a chat, without being intrusive. After moving inside we enjoyed an also wonderful dessert plus a finishing coffee and Drambuie. All in all it made a wonderful evening, compliments to Restaurant De Veldhoeve.

reviews.title: Lunch for 60 years married couple
reviews.text: For us a second time to visit this restaurant, now to celebrate a 60 years married couple. We started outside with a welcome drink. The table inside was nicely dressed up. A lunch (salmon or beefsteak) was served by friendly personnel and the atmosphere was excellent. And everyone enjoy the delicious meal with a finishing special dessert.

reviews.title: Surprisingly good food in a historic farm building.
reviews.text: Went there for a celebration dinner, and we're the only guests. But the waiter managed to make us feel very relaxed. Very professional and knows his wine. One of our party is a vegetarian, and there was not really any vegetarian food on the menu, the chef created so really nice food, with the ingredients he had. Very professional. The rest of the food was also extremely nice. Great flavours and textures. We will be back!

reviews.title: Wonderful warm atmosphere and special service from the chef
reviews.text: Excellent quality of food, with service which is unusual for the Netherlands which was outstanding. The warm atmosphere of the resturant is really welcoming.

reviews.title: Fabulous!
reviews.text: At at this restaurant last night whilst out house hunting, it was fantastic, had veal it was delicious , highly recommend it , well done to the lovely lady who served us and to the chef. Will be back for sure.

reviews.title: Perfection
reviews.text:
The hospitality, the quality of the food is perfect. The "farm-atmosphere" is chique.
We celebrated our wedding-diner with 40 family and friends

reviews.title: Always excellent
reviews.text:
We always comes here for dinner every time we are in Epe, top service and very good food. 

Thank you for making us always special and for the gift.

reviews.title: Cosy rural friendly atmosphere
reviews.text:
Very friendly staff serving fine dishes which are well balanced and eatem in an very old but very cosy accomodation (old traditional Veluwe style  farm, nicely rebuild into a cosy small scale restauramt.
If you want to be well treated with pleasant staff serving good food, go there !

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

I’ve always loved train travel. There’s something special about settling into a window seat and watching the landscape drift past. And as a wheelchair user, that joy only grows when the journey feels easy: level boarding, space to move, and the kind of accessibility that lets you fully relax. For me, the best train rides—like weaving through the Tuscan countryside on Trenitalia—are never just a way to get from A to B; they're part of the adventure.

articleContent.title: Your family-friendly guide to Greenville, SC

seoInfo.metaDescription: Picnics, waterparks, museums, festivals, and plenty of unexpected all-ages activities—the equation for the perfect family getaway can be tough to balance. But there’s one place that does just this, promising plenty of memories to pack along with the souvenirs. Greenville, South Carolina checks all of the boxes, from hotels with plenty of family-friendly amenities to museums with interactive exhibits that’ll hold everyone’s attention (even a rambunctious toddler). Those in charge of packing can breathe easy: the weather is great year-round—the hottest month is July with temps up to 89 degrees, and the coolest is January, when the high hits around 55 degrees.

tripContent.title: Santa Fe: heritage & history on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Looking for adventure on the original Route 66? Santa Fe, the oldest state capital, is a must-stop for history buffs. The city, founded in 1610, is older than the United States—but the area has been populated for well over a thousand years. With so much history and heritage, you'll want to allow plenty of time to explore the best of the Southwest—so here are 12 suggestions for things to see, do, and learn.

tripContent.title: Discover Louisville’s global cuisine at these hidden gems
tripContent.description: When it comes to your taste buds, Louisville’s lively food scene invites you to adventure beyond city limits. Plan your culinary exploration with this roundup of the city’s most-loved eateries, serving classic and creative dishes inspired by food and festivities from around the world.

articleContent.title: Where to find the best croissants in Paris

seoInfo.metaDescription: Croissant lovers, unite! This guide delivers the best Parisian croissants and tells you where to try them all.

The perfect itinerary for this sprawling, chaotic metropolis. We’ve alternated visits to ancient landmarks with stops in cool neighborhoods where you can slow down and sip the ouzo. All along the way, we’ve included highly rated picks from the Tripadvisor community to make sure that your trip is as iconic as Athens itself.

With 5 days in Paris, you can see much more than the Eiffel Tower and the Louvre Museum. This itinerary is packed with plenty of activities you can choose from, great for both first-timers and return visitors.
